### Phase 1 — Wire Auth (Frontend ↔ Backend)

**What:** Connect the already-built backend auth system to the frontend.

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.jsx`
- Provide `user`, `token`, `login()`, `logout()`, `refreshToken()` to the entire app
- JWT stored **in-memory** (not localStorage); refresh token via httpOnly cookie on `/auth/refresh`
- Auto-refresh on 401 response

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/pages/Login.jsx` + `Login.module.css`
- Centered card layout, email + password fields, Google OAuth button
- Calls `POST /auth/login`, stores JWT in `AuthContext`
- Redirects to `/dashboard` on success

#### [NEW] `frontend/src/pages/Register.jsx` + `Register.module.css`
- Email + password with strength meter, AI data consent checkbox
- Calls `POST /auth/register`

#### [MODIFY] `frontend/src/utils/api.js` → `frontend/src/lib/api/client.js`
- Replace `X-Session-ID` header with `Authorization: Bearer <token>` from `AuthContext`
- Add auto-retry with token refresh on 401
- Create typed files: `auth.js`, `datasets.js`, `pipeline.js`, `dashboards.js`, `history.js` per resource

#### [MODIFY] `frontend/src/App.jsx`
- Add `<AuthContext.Provider>` wrapping all routes
- Add protected route wrapper (redirect to `/login` if no valid token)
- Add `/login`, `/register` routes

